Kathy van Coppenhagen (Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A grandmother from Sundra in Mpumalanga who tried to hide from her attackers in a dog kennel after she was shot four times last week, has died.Kathleen (Kathy) van Coppenhagen and her husband Frik, both in their late fifties, were attacked on their smallholding when they took their bullmastiffs outside at about 23:00 on Friday, Netwerk24 reported.Police spokesperson Salom&eacute; van der Westhuizen said Van Coppenhagen was kept outsde while her husband was taken into the house to open the safe. Her husband heard the four shots but could do nothing because the robbers had tied him up and put a bag over his face.He later managed to free himself and went looking for his wife. He found her in the kennel with four bullet wounds.He then ran to the neighbours and the police were called.Kathy was taken to hospital where she fought for her life, but she died on Wednesday evening.Her daughter Samantha Willemse said on Thursday that she was having a tough day and didn&rsquo;t want to talk about the matter.The police are investigating a case of house robbery and murder.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.